data.name: Help_DestinationAddress
data.value: The address for handling routed requests.

data.name: Help_DisableDestinationCertificateValidation
data.value: Accept any certificate from destinations using HTTPS.

data.name: Help_FirstAlphabetical
data.value: Always picks the first destination in order that is available. Useful for active / passive failover.
data.comment: App uses custom ordering to ensure destination order is maintained which is why alphabetical order is not mentioned.

data.name: Help_HealthAddress
data.value: Optional: Add to perform active health checks.

data.name: Help_LeastRequests
data.value: Routes requests to the destination currently handling the fewest active requests.

data.name: Help_NameDescription
data.value: Short name and and optional description.

data.name: Help_PowerOfTwoChoices
data.value: Picks two random destinations and sends the request to the one with fewer active requests. This avoids the overhead of Least Requests and the worst case for Random where it selects a busy destination.

data.name: Help_Random
data.value: Sends each request to a randomly chosen destination.

data.name: Help_RoundRobin
data.value: Cycles through destinations in order, giving each one a turn.

data.name: Help_StickySessions
data.value: Use a cookie to keep a client connected to same destination.

data.value: Choose if the management site will be available remotely. Pro tip: This setting can be left on localhost and have the management site be remotely accessible via the reverse proxy by adding a Cluster with 127.0.0.1 (or ::1) and the above HTTPS port as the destination and a corresponding route.

data.value: Enables an HTTP connection tarpit that deliberately delays unmatched traffic responses by a randomized duration between 15 and 30 seconds, slowing down abusive or unwanted clients. Note that each stalled connection still consumes server resources, which may impact overall capacity under load.

data.name: WARN_RestartProxy
data.value:
This will restart the proxy server and the management site.
All connections will be closed. Useful for flushing connections using old certificates.
This does not restart the host OS.
Continue with restart?

data.name: WARN_ShutdownProxy

This utility allows you to purge a certificate from the disk and the database.
If the certificate is used in the current candidate configuration, remove it from use first or you will not be allowed to continue.
If the certificate selected is currently in use in the running configuration, you must first commit a new configuration that does not use the certificate.
If the certificate was used in any prior configuration, you will be prompted to select a new certificate to take its place so that prior configurations remain valid.
